`program-2/series-8/formal/P2S8.lean` — Program 2 Series 8 (2.8), THE COMMON GOOD (aggregator).

Imports the five workstreams. Series 2.8 is the value CAPSTONE and the last series of Phase 2. It asks: across many
selves, does local pairwise coherence GLUE into a global good, or can it be FRUSTRATED — every pair reconciled, yet no
global section? It builds FRESH, model-derived off the directed attention, one thing: the GOOD (a self-relative
valuation, WS1), the RECONCILIATION (a translation by the signed directed-attention increment, WS2), and the HOLONOMY
of those reconciliations around a cycle (WS3), all read off the SAME increment `incr` — a function of the attention
alone. It finds, HONESTLY: the good is non-trivial and perspectival (WS1); local coherence is pervasive (WS2); the
obstruction is genuinely many-body (vanishing for two selves) and model-derived (killed by symmetrising the
attention), not a single edge, not import-ness, not a bolted-on gadget (WS3); and the fork is genuine — a directed
3-ring FRUSTRATES (`hol = 3`, no global section) while a mutual star GLUES (`hol = 0`, a global section), both
reachable, neither by fiat (WS4). The verdict is computed (WS5): FRUSTRATED — local coherence does not force a global
good, the value analog of energy's global failure (2.7). No common good is written into this universe; it is made,
edge by edge, and never owed.
-/
